  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "14. ye shall pass … armed—that is, officered or marshalled under five leaders in the old and approved caravan order (see on [174]Ex 13:18).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "all the mighty men of valour—The words are not to be interpreted strictly as meaning the whole, but only the flower or choice of the fighting men (see on [175]Jos 4:12).   ",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "They answered, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " i.e. the Reubenites, &c., mentioned ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " Joshua 1:12",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 1:12",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", to whom Joshua’s discourse is confined, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bldvs",
        "text": " Joshua 1:13-15",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Joshua 1:13-15",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". No doubt the other tribes expressed the same thing; but this is only recorded concerning these, because that might seem most doubtful, and the obedience of the rest was unquestionable. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And they answered Joshua,.... The two tribes of Gad and Reuben, and the half tribe of Manasseh, the heads of them, such as were deputed for that purpose, and were their mouths to him: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "saying, all that thou commandest we will do; with respect to this affair of going over Jordan with their brethren, to assist them in the conquest of the land of Canaan: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and whithersoever thou sendest us, we will go; in what position he would have them be in the army, and to whatsoever part of the country he should send them to subdue, and to whatsoever city he should order them to besiege. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and whithersoever thou sendest us, we will go; in what position he would have them be in the army, and to whatsoever part of the country he should send them to subdue, and to whatsoever city he should order them to besiege. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
